joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"30ce7299de193fb5f5af79d38703fe2b3d8cea8e427ea2c6fb0d19cc3c9d43e2","event_uuid":"9e4c187c-0dfc-413f-bd72-9d31a53d4eb5","position":{"commit_sha":"9c53b43bc6972c96066b10ff8d8c8d0febf33a50","position":"1784838256503281997-9e4c187c-0dfc-413f-bd72-9d31a53d4eb5"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"789fcc6ff99a0d0d3be0b3fa637aac490e77027b2e127af02bbfe4bed6497bfe","event_uuid":"2025a159-a14e-4133-b9d1-42f455f40660","position":{"commit_sha":"cb720ac76cf2c624a22a266d3e773770ebdbb7f8","position":"1784844605924080001-2025a159-a14e-4133-b9d1-42f455f40660"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"fe7a562cdff22e902784c33a71f0712a1d9e4c7b54084eb4360ccfe1b4c145de","event_uuid":"1cd5255e-db16-4346-a2ff-a8db212dc53d","position":{"commit_sha":"21f080e25a98f8aee1c8feea24eff50ed431c942","position":"1784846012657158001-1cd5255e-db16-4346-a2ff-a8db212dc53d"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"1a82a2f255ed0f88538f98e82c915f00a291662eb34faf00f9b62cf7e48752bd","event_uuid":"cb1d9b30-712f-4464-8e9f-1e4eb9bbcc38","position":{"commit_sha":"14140f28de7613bb3d7a9b901fe8ffd7c73071f6","position":"1784847272537760001-cb1d9b30-712f-4464-8e9f-1e4eb9bbcc38"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-218_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"cbe2d483-8609-4f4e-ba56-db538f86808d","comments":[],"created_at":1784820305785606001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[],"description":"## Context / Problem\n\nThe outbound link differ compares in vendor shape. `outbound_links.py:30` imports\n`_RELATION_TO_JIRA_LINK` from `adapters.jira.jira_fields`; `_existing_jira_links`\n(`outbound_links.py:38-63`) reads the raw vendor `fields.issuelinks` list\n(`{type:{name}, inwardIssue:{key}, outwardIssue:{key}}`) into a `(type_name, other_key)` set;\nand `_diff_links` translates relation→`(jira_type, swap)` inline at `outbound_links.py:105`.\nEpic bbf1 AC3 requires zero `adapters.jira` imports in core, and ADR 0035 §(d) requires that\ncore compare only canonical shapes (vendor payloads cross core opaquely, produced/consumed by\nport calls at the boundaries — the same principle the sibling canonical field-diff story pins\nfor fields).\n\n## Approach\n\nMove both link translations onto the `SupportsLinks` capability (adapter-side, translation\nonly — neither member is parameterized on a shape a non-Jira backend lacks):\n\n- `map_remote_links(remote_fields)` → the canonical link set: entries of\n  `(relation, remote_key, opaque_vendor_type)`. The Jira implementation absorbs today's\n  `_existing_jira_links` (`outbound_links.py:38-63`) including its direction-agnostic dedup\n  (`:57-62`), translating vendor link-type names back to canonical relations via the adapter's\n  own map; remote link types with no canonical relation are returned with `relation=None` so\n  core continues to ignore them for matching and never removes them (today's semantics).\n  The `opaque_vendor_type` passenger is carried untouched by core solely for the REMOVE\n  payload's `type` key.\n- `link_payload_for_relation(relation)` → `(vendor_type, swap)` — the emission translation,\n  replacing the inline `_RELATION_TO_JIRA_LINK.get(relation)` at `outbound_links.py:105`.\n\nCore `_diff_links`/`_diff_link_removals` (`outbound_links.py:66-135` and `:138-199`) then\ncompare local `ticket[\"deps\"]` (`{target_id, relation, link_uuid}`) against the canonical set\nin relation vocabulary. Emitted ADD/REMOVE payload keys are unchanged (ADD\n`outbound_links.py:119-128`, REMOVE `:196-197`), so the link apply path is untouched.\n`_RELATION_TO_JIRA_LINK` becomes adapter-internal. The AST neutrality gate in\n`tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py` is extended to assert zero\n`adapters.jira` imports in `outbound_links.py`.\n\nRejected alternatives: (a) keeping the vendor link diff in core (violates §(d) and AC3);\n(b) a port method that accepts the vendor issuelinks dict *and* the local deps and returns\nthe diff — that moves diffing onto the port, the exact violation class plan review blocked\non ticket 97f2's prior attempt (core owns diff; the port only translates).\n\n## Scope\n\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_backend.py (SupportsLinks: map_remote_links + link_payload_for_relation)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_links.py (canonical comparison; drop vendor import)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/backend.py (implement the two members)\n- src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/jira_fields.py (_RELATION_TO_JIRA_LINK becomes adapter-internal; reverse map)\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py (AST gate extended to outbound_links.py)\n- tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/ (link-diff behavior tests)\n\n## Testing\n\n- Happy path: a local dep missing remotely emits an ADD with today's exact payload keys and\n  values (`type`, `to_key`, `relation`, `swap`, `link_uuid`); a dep present remotely (either\n  direction) emits nothing.\n- Edge/failure: unknown remote link types are ignored for matching and never removed;\n  removals remain managed-ref gated (`outbound_links.py:138-199` semantics); REMOVE payload\n  carries the original vendor type name via the opaque passenger.\n- Gate: the extended AST case fails if `outbound_links.py` re-grows an `adapters.jira`\n  import.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] `outbound_links.py` contains NO `adapters.jira` import (module-level or\n      function-nested) — verified by the extended AST case in\n      `tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py`.\n- [ ] Link diffing compares canonical relations only; vendor link-type names appear in core\n      solely as opaque payload passengers — verified by code review + the behavior tests in\n      Testing (identical ADD/REMOVE payloads to today).\n- [ ] `make lint && make typecheck && make test` green; whole test tree collects with 0 errors.\n\n## Plan-review remediation (drift re-review, G1G2 findings)\n\nTwo gaps are pinned here:\n\n1. **`outbound_differ.py` is in scope.** `compute_outbound_mutations` (in `outbound_differ.py`)\n   calls `_diff_links(ticket, jira_fields, binding_store)` at the update path. That call site\n   must additionally pass the configured backend's `SupportsLinks` capability so `_diff_links`\n   / `_diff_link_removals` can translate via `map_remote_links` / `link_payload_for_relation`.\n   The backend is already in scope there (threaded for the field diff). So:\n   `src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_differ.py` is ADDED to Scope — it passes the\n   `SupportsLinks` capability as the new 4th argument to `_diff_links`.\n\n2. **The ADD dedup stays DIRECTION-AGNOSTIC.** Today `_existing_jira_links` inserts\n   `(jira_type_name, other_key)` for the key present on EITHER `inwardIssue` OR `outwardIssue`,\n   so a Jira link of a given type between the local issue and key K dedups a local dep to K\n   REGARDLESS of which side K is on (verified: a local `blocks`→K dep against an INWARD Blocks\n   link from K emits nothing today). The canonical set from `map_remote_links` carries the\n   `opaque_vendor_type` passenger precisely so this is preserved: the core ADD dedup matches a\n   local dep against a canonical entry on **`(opaque_vendor_type, remote_key)`** — the\n   direction-agnostic pair equal to today's `(type_name, other_key)` — NOT on `(relation,\n   remote_key)`. `link_payload_for_relation(relation)` yields the local dep's `(vendor_type,\n   swap)`, and the dedup compares that `vendor_type` + target key against the canonical\n   entries' `(opaque_vendor_type, remote_key)`. The `relation` field of a canonical entry\n   drives ONLY the direction-SPECIFIC REMOVE managed-gate matching (mirroring today's\n   `resolve_inbound_link`-based REMOVE). `map_remote_links` still applies today's\n   direction-agnostic dedup internally (it may return one canonical entry per\n   `(vendor_type, remote_key)`).\n\n**Added acceptance criteria:**\n- [ ] The ADD dedup is direction-agnostic: a local dep to K dedups against a remote link of the\n      mapped vendor type between the local issue and K whether K is the inward or the outward\n      side — verified by a held-out test (inward remote link vs outward local dep -> no ADD),\n      matching today's behavior byte-for-byte.\n- [ ] `outbound_differ.py` passes the `SupportsLinks` capability into `_diff_links`; the AST\n      neutrality gate still passes for `outbound_differ.py` (the capability is the injected\n      backend, not an `adapters.jira` import).\n\n## Landed\n\nImplemented and merged to `main` as Gerrit change 935 (LLM-Review +1, Verified +1).","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/_backend.py","reason":"SupportsLinks: map_remote_links + link_payload_for_relation"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/outbound_links.py","reason":"canonical relation comparison; drop vendor import"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/backend.py","reason":"implement the two link members"},{"path":"src/rebar/_engine/rebar_reconciler/adapters/jira/jira_fields.py","reason":"_RELATION_TO_JIRA_LINK adapter-internal + reverse map"},{"path":"tests/unit/rebar_reconciler/test_backend_neutrality.py","reason":"AST gate extended to outbound_links.py"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["parent","bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a"]],"parent_id":"bbf1-82e1-cf9d-494a","parent_status_uuid":"02b6e738-580c-4b2c-8f5b-bf0ae0b46aef","plan_review_phase":"execution","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":[],"ticket_id":"eefd-49b1-995f-488d","ticket_type":"story","title":"Canonical link diff: SupportsLinks translation members replace vendor link-shape comparison in outbound_links","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["5c035aa4-64a0-4d85-ab11-40beeb67dc9a","b5164341-5ff3-4a25-b60e-44fdb06d2dfe","6eab5f7c-4490-4ab2-9c25-899f966394f1","fb1e59e2-19fe-47e3-8a4a-c0b92a44fae7","6c9effff-fc14-44a0-943e-a1688e71d584","02b6e738-580c-4b2c-8f5b-bf0ae0b46aef","75142a6a-f73a-40a0-8d8e-268924963e77","9e4c187c-0dfc-413f-bd72-9d31a53d4eb5","2025a159-a14e-4133-b9d1-42f455f40660","1cd5255e-db16-4346-a2ff-a8db212dc53d","cb1d9b30-712f-4464-8e9f-1e4eb9bbcc38"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784847272537760002,"uuid":"e0af0d82-0673-451d-9b77-d2d33a2c6813"}